{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632985","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632985"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:47:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:47:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17452"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17452","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17452"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10142"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70895"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10142","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10142"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17452"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56362"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5517"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23742"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23828"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70895","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70895"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare delivery in correctional facilities presents unique challenges due to the confined environment and complex health needs of the prison population.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a fundamental principle of prison healthcare?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Healthcare delivery should be modified to suit institutional requirements","Prisoners should receive care equivalent to community standards","Healthcare access should be determined by security classification","Treatment should focus on communicable disease prevention","Care should prioritise rehabilitation over acute treatment"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer reflects the principle of equivalence - \u003Cstrong\u003Eprisoners should receive care equivalent to community standards\u003C/strong\u003E. This is a fundamental human right and ethical principle in correctional healthcare. Despite their incarceration, prisoners retain their right to healthcare.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHealthcare delivery should be modified to suit institutional requirements\u003C/strong\u003E: while practical adaptations may be necessary, the standard of care should not be compromised by institutional constraints.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHealthcare access should be determined by security classification\u003C/strong\u003E: access to healthcare is a fundamental right that applies regardless of security status.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment should focus on communicable disease prevention\u003C/strong\u003E: while important in the prison setting, healthcare must address all medical needs comprehensively.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECare should prioritise rehabilitation over acute treatment\u003C/strong\u003E: while rehabilitation is important, it should not come at the expense of other healthcare needs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPrison healthcare services must balance security requirements with the delivery of appropriate medical care while maintaining professional standards and ethical principles.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Prison populations have higher rates of mental illness, substance use disorders, and infectious diseases compared to the general population.","The principle of equivalence states that prisoners should receive healthcare of equal quality to that available in the community.","Continuity of care between prison and community health services is essential for successful prisoner health outcomes."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021.","Wolf G, Bagaric M. Addressing a Human Rights Crisis: Health Care for Prisoners in Australia. J Law Med. 2024;31(1):42-69.","Watson R, Stimpson A, Hostick T. Prison health care: a review of the literature. Int J Nurs Stud. 2004;41(2):119-128. doi:10.1016/s0020-7489(03)00128-7"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56362"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17452"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56362","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56362"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T15:03:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T15:04:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10142"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70895"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","